1.name: addtobasket_source
1.description: Source of the add-to-basket action (user-add,system-add). Source of the add-to-basket action. Values: user clicked a button add-to-basket = user-add,the product is added by the restored basket function = system-add. Every productID in an product add needs a product-add source. If multiple products are added,as many product-add sources need to be passed. Seperate them by a semicolon. Add source must be in same order as the passed productIDs. Example: 1 Product with an addition is added to the basket. cp12 = user-add; system-add

2.description: Completed Baskets. Hybirs BasketID. Hybris basket ID should be passed only once per completed basket. It is passed when user indicates that he wants to checkout. (Usually when he clicks the "to checkout" button on the basket page.) At that point all modifiactions to the basket (adding or deleting products,adding a coupon code,...) have been made. Where is parameter passed: The basket ID is passed on the next page of the checkout process. Some examples for the next page (depending on login status of customer): Sample Page (if existent),Login Page,Last Check Page,Address Page,Payment Page,... Please see tracking concepts and ticket w/ attached word file (under comments) for further information. When is parameter passed: if user clicks "to checkout" button or does a similar action that indicates him to go to checkout. AND the parameter is empty OR filled with a different ID (in case of Multi-Buyers). If the paramter is filled with the same ID,it is not passed again.
2.name: basket_id

3.name: category01
3.description: Hierachical structure information: 1st Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 2nd level of breadcrumbs)

4.description: Hierachical structure information: 2nd Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 3rd level of breadcrumbs)
4.name: category02

5.name: category03
5.description: Hierachical structure information: 3rd Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 4th level of breadcrumbs)

6.name: category04
6.description: Hierachical structure information: 4th Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 5th level of breadcrumbs)

7.name: category05
7.description: Hierachical structure information: 5th Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 6th level of breadcrumbs)

8.name: category06
8.description: Hierachical structure information: 6th Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 7th level of breadcrumbs)

9.name: category07
9.description: Hierachical structure information: 7th Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 8th level of breadcrumbs)

10.name: category08
10.description: Hierachical structure information: 8th Level of Page Categories (usually corresponding to the 9th level of breadcrumbs)

11.description: Usage of the product list filters at the category pages. Parameter relates to the filter above the results listing. (Currently this is only "Brand" or "Type".) Filters from the regular search filter are passed in page parameters 6 & 8. When customer filters selection through the top level filters (Brand or Type),the filter and its value are passed to Webtrekk with the request of the reloaded page. Usually that is either Brand or Type with the appropriate value. If both can be chosen at the same time,the information needs to be passed comma seperated. If nothing is filtered,please to not pass this parameter to Webtrekk.
11.name: category_filter

13.name: category_sort
13.description: Used sort function of product lists at the category pages.Syntax: SortOption_SortDirection

14.name: content_id
14.description: unique and human readable name of the page/screen

17.name: customer_birthday
17.description: Date of birth [YYYYMMDD]. Date of birth in YYYYMMDD format if information is available (user added information to his profile)

18.name: customer_gender
18.description: Gender,if available (user added information to his profile): male = 1,female = 2. not transmitted if information is unavailable

20.name: customer_login_status
20.description: Captures the current login status on every page: Soft Logged-In = User was logged-in in previous session and did not log out (is greeted with name in header),Logged-In = User has actively logged-in,Logged-Out = User does not have any of the above status

21.name: customer_mail
21.description: md5 Hash Value of the Customer Email address

22.name: customer_scoring
22.description: Reason Code is transmitted as provided by scoring service provider. Usually captured at the Payment Method Pages and the Order Check Page of registered customers. Indicates the calculation/reason of the shown payment methods.

23.name: customer_status
23.description: Identifies the status of a customer on every page. Status must be written in CAPS. If not specified otherwhise,status changes are measured with the next page request. Status remains the same after a change,until the user acively switches into another status. XX = as long as user has not identified himself as any of the other 3 status or if he has logged out within the session,RC = if user logs into an existing account,WI = if user chooses the Walk-in Option on the Checkout Login Page,NC = if user chooses to create a new account (status changes on the form page).

24.description: Identifies the status of a customer on every page. Status must be written in CAPS. If not specified otherwhise,status changes are measured with the next page request. Status remains the same after a change,until the user acively switches into another status. XX = as long as user has not identified himself as any of the other 3 status or if he has logged out within the session,RC = if user logs into an existing account,WI = if user chooses the Walk-in Option on the Checkout Login Page,NC = if user chooses to create a new account (status changes on the form page).
24.name: customer_status_hmc

26.description: Counter for Beauty Card registrations. Passes value 1 to Webtrekk for a successful Beauty Card registration.
26.name: dbc_counter

27.name: delivering_system
27.description: System that is delivering the page or feature.

28.description: Type of delivery address: billingaddress | otheraddress | packstation | pickupbycustomer | postfiliale | foreign_gift_delivery | … Pass delivery address type chosen by the customer at time of order. See
28.name: delivery_address_type

29.description: Type of delivery mode: de_default_delivery_mode | de_vst_pickup_mode | de_express12h_delivery_mode | de_download_shipping_delivery_mode | de_foreign_gift_delivery_mode. Pass delivery mode type chosen by the customer at time of order. See "values" for corresponding values.
29.name: delivery_mode

30.description: Discount code of the redeemed discount. Pass code of redeemed discount (or giveaway). If multiple codes are redeemed
30.name: discount_code

31.name: discount_value
31.description: Granted discount value in local currency. Discount value in local currency. Use dot as decimal delimiter. DONOT use a thausend delimiter. (value must be parsed as string?) If discount is a percentage,please calculate correctly. Do not pass percentages in this parameter.

32.description: Displayed text of error messages or validation/error information if no text is displayed to the user. List of strings (delimiter: semicolon ";"),e.g. "Error1";"Error2"
32.name: error_message

33.description: Captures any Error Code delivered to th/backend.  Format = Error Object : Error Code. Captures any Error Code delivered to the frontend/backend.  Format = Error Object : Error Code. If multiple errors need to be passed,please seperate by a semicolon. (i.e. "DouglasCard:25;Play:recommendations")
33.name: error_object_code

35.name: fragance_consultant_settings
35.description: List of comma-separated attributes used to generate the fragrance consultant result list. Please use the same order of attributes when passing this parameter. A change of order would lead to a different string that cannot properly be matched in Webtrekk.

36.description: Value of gift vouchers used during buying process. The sum of all debited gift vouchers. Do NOT use a thousand delimiter! When no gift voucher was used that value is 0.00.
36.name: gift_voucher_value

37.name: gift_voucher_value_orderd
37.description: Value of the ordered gift voucher. The sum of all gift vouchers bought. Do NOT use a thousand delimiter!

38.name: greeting_card_motive
38.description: Motive of the greeting card. Captured with the order

39.name: layer_name
39.description: Catpures the names of layers shown to the users. Layers are defined as dynamic overlay elements which provides possibilities to the users but do not lead them to other pages or activities. Example: MyDouglas Login Layer

40.description: Kind of Discount (please see Ticket ITDEV-445)
40.name: level

41.name: major_touchpoints
41.description: Which major (initiative) touchpoints has the user had during his visit? i.e. Color Catcher. Helps w/ attribution of additional revenue to initiatives.

42.name: newsletter_counter
42.description: Counter for Newsletter Double Opt-ins. Passes value 1 to Webtrekk on Newsletter Double Opt-in Page fo a successful double opt-in.

43.name: order_id
43.description: Hybris Order ID. OrderID is passed

44.description: Bijective Page ID of the displayed page. For Hybris Pages this is usually the Hybris Page ID (b or c number). For Play an appropriate bijective ID mus be defined.
44.name: page_id

45.name: page_mvt
45.description: Captures if a page is generated/manipulated by a Testing Tool.

47.description: Payment Method used to order. Payment used for the order. Examples: Invoice (Rechnung) = INVOICE
47.name: payment_method

48.description: Paymment methods shown to user (comma seperated,lowercase). Please do not confuse this with cp32. cp32 holds the same information but is seperated by a semicolon so Webtrekk can transpose it into single payment methods.
48.name: payment_methods_offered

49.description: Information on what triggered the page impression. Used to identifiy additional PIs of a page. On Category Pages or Searches. If the Page Impression is triggered by a navigation object or by filter/sort/ajax reloads: initial = initial call
49.name: pi_trigger

50.name: product_additional_information
50.description: Captures additional information related to products. The additional information is captured as descriptive text value. Examples: if a product is bundled with an adittion,values: yes / no,if a product is labled with a price bubble,value: price bubble. Use a semikolon to seperate the values for each product. For multiple productIDs in an order please use the same order as the productIDs.

51.name: product_additions
51.description: Captures if a product has additions or not (no | color variants | size variants | style variants). Pass one value per product. Use same order as product IDs. Use semicolon as delimiter.

52.description: Product Availability Status as perceived by the customer (Available | Soon back in stock | Sold out | Coming soon). Product availability status as seen on the product detail page (or whereever prodcut ist viewed). If multiple products are passed
52.name: product_availability_status

54.name: product_filter
54.description: Ordered list (combination) of name:value pairs of used filters and values. Order criteria is the sequence of usage. If multiple values are selected within a filter the delimiter between the values is || (logical OR operator). Delimiter between filter is comma. 1. single value selection: filtername1:filtervalue1,filtername2:filtervalue2 2. List of filters with one multiple value selection: filtername1:filtervalue1||filtervalue2,filtername2:filtervalue2 Default Value:

55.description: Shall product be wrapped? (Gift| No Gift) Capured for every product when capturing the order. Use a semikolon to seperate the values for each product. For multiple productIDs in an order please use the same order as the productIDs.
55.name: product_gift

57.description: Product IDs of products added or deleted from Wishlist. Transmitted to Webtrekk when the corresponding layer (add or deletion) is shown. This parameter must not be used alone. To identify addition or deletion from list please cross reference with the corresponding layer parameter. Product IDs of products added or deleted from Whislist. Transmitted to Webtrekk when the corresponding layer (add or deletion) is shown. This parameter must not be used alone. To identify addition or deletion from list please cross reference with the corresponding layer parameter (= Overlays (pP17)). To be set when the corresponding layer (add or deletion) is shown.
57.name: product_id_wishlist

58.name: product_interaction
58.description: Product interaction type. When interacting with a product,the status needs to be set correctly: User views a product = view,a product is added to the basket = add,a product is ordered = conf. Product views currently usually occur on product detail pages. Product adds can be done by either the user or the system (permanent basket,additions,...). If two product interactions accur at the same time,a request for every single status needs to be pushed to Webtrekk. (i.e. Entering the page on a product detail page and having a permanent basket. -> view of product on PD Page,add of products from the permanent basket). If two requests are pushed into Webtrekk,both need to hold all relevant page information. If no status is passed with a productID,Webtrekk will count this as view. Therefore a status must be passed on all product interactions!

61.description: List of prices of products in local currency. List of numbers (max 2. decimal places,decimal delimiter
61.name: product_price

62.name: product_quantity
62.description: Quantity of each product. Passed on every product interaction

63.name: product_quantity_opr
63.description: Quantity of products reserved via OPR (Online Product Reservation) for pickup in store. Only passed on 'OPR - Confirmation' Layer.Currently only one product is reservable within one product reservation progress. As in future it maybe will be possible to reserve more than one product,we decided to use integer values,which can be analyzed more detailed in Webtrekk.

66.description: Captures if a product has variants or not. If yes,it is differentiated between color and size variants (yes | no). Pass one value per product. Use same order as product IDs. Use semicolon as delimiter.
66.name: product_variants

67.description: The Product View Type. Describes the place/way the product view occured. Examples: Product Quick View
67.name: product_view_type

68.description: Used search criterias. Name:value pairs. Delimiter Semikolon. Used filters and values. Name:value pairs. Delimiter between filter is Semikolon. Delimieter between multiple values is: || (logical OR). 1. single value selection: filtername:filtervalue 2. multiple value selection: filtername:filtervalue1||filtervalue2 Default Value:
68.name: search_criteria

69.name: search_filter_usage
69.description: Distinguishes between an initial and an adjusted search e.g. by filter usage. To be set on pageload on search result pages. Set

71.description: Search phrase of internal search. The search phrase is passed on every page that is triggered by a search or search modification. This also holds true if the "result" page is a landing page like "Color Expert" or a product detail page. If searche technology (Factfinder) is used on category pages or similar = use default values such as: "default_category" or "default_brand". Please see tracking concepts for further information. Please use lowercases for search terms. Spaces may be included into single search phrases.
